Method Detail

createSnmpTrap

public SNMPTrap createSnmpTrap()
Creates an SNMP trap that matches the trap definition stored in this object. Varbinds with a wildcard will have a random number in place of the wildcard. SNMPv1 time ticks will have a random value. No varbind type will be specified. SNMPv3 traps are currently not supported.

The SNMPHost stored in the trap is generic and should be replaced before use.

Returns:
- SNMPTrap that matches this trap definition or null if there is an error with the actual trap definition
